# Settings System

Settings control how LexMastery behaves at runtime.

They must be flexible but safe.

---

# Product Vision

Settings must:

- give users control
- protect privacy
- configure AI behavior
- manage notifications
- allow UI customization

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

SettingsController (Riverpod)

↓

SettingsState

↓

SettingsRepository

↓

Local Storage + API Sync

---

# State Management

SettingsState includes:

- loading
- loaded
- updating
- error

Core Data:

- themeMode
- notificationSettings
- privacySettings
- aiBehaviorSettings
- accessibilitySettings

---

# Settings Categories

1. Appearance
2. Notifications
3. Privacy
4. AI Behavior
5. Accessibility
6. Account

---

# AI Behavior Settings

User can control:

- explanation depth
- verbosity level
- tutoring mode intensity
- suggestion frequency

---

# Notification Settings

- study reminders
- exam alerts
- AI suggestions
- streak notifications

---

# Privacy Settings

- data sharing
- analytics opt-in
- AI memory control

---

# Navigation Rules

Settings accessible from:

- Profile
- Dashboard

---

# Offline Behaviour

- settings fully accessible offline
- changes queued for sync

---

# API Contracts

GET /settings

PUT /settings/update

POST /settings/sync

---

# Analytics Events

settings_view

settings_update

ai_behavior_changed

notification_preferences_updated

---

# UI Composition Rules

Settings UI must include:

- categorized sections
- toggles
- sliders (AI behavior)
- confirmation dialogs for sensitive changes

---

# UX Rules

- avoid overwhelming users
- group logically
- provide defaults

---

# Error Handling

- retry sync silently
- preserve local state

---

# Performance

- instant toggle response
- deferred sync allowed

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader navigation
- keyboard toggles
- clear labels

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Settings updates

AI behavior logic

Notification toggles

Widget Tests:

Settings screen

Toggle components

Section grouping

Integration Tests:

Full settings sync flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating settings features:

- always allow offline changes
- always respect user privacy settings
- always make AI behavior configurable
- never force AI behavior changes without user consent